    <text>
        <group>
            <text type="letter" xml:lang="ru">
                <body>
                    <opener rend="right"><dateline><date when-custom="1789-09-12">Сентября 12-го
                                числа 1789 г.</date></dateline><salute rend="inline">Любезная
                            внучка!</salute></opener>
                    <p>По выздоровления <rs ref="people.xml#mar03">сестрицы вашей</rs><note
                            type="editorial">In September 1789, <ref target="people.xml#mar03"
                                >Mariya Pavlovna</ref> was inoculated for smallpox just like her
                            elder siblings had been, but she suffered a worse case of the disease
                            than the others did. (See Catherine's letters to little '<ref
                                target="people.xml#mar03">Machoutka</ref>''s mother, <ref
                                target="people.xml#mar02">Mariya Fedorovna</ref>, <bibl><title
                                    ref="works.xml#sborni01">SIRIO</title>, <biblScope unit="vol"
                                    >xv</biblScope>, <biblScope unit="pp">pp.
                                160-66</biblScope></bibl>.) According to Catherine, the inoculation
                            had deleterious effects on the young girl's looks: a year later, on 18
                            September 1790, Catherine wrote to <ref target="people.xml#gri01"
                                >Grimm</ref> about <ref target="people.xml#mar03">Mariya</ref>:
                            'celle-ci devait être un garçon: la petite-vérole inoculée l'a gâtée
                            totalement; elle a tous les traits grossis; elle est comme un dragon'
                            ('this one should have been a boy. The smallpox inoculation ruined her
                            completely; all her features are swollen. She is like a dragon')
                                    (<bibl><title ref="works.xml#sborni01">SIRIO</title>, <biblScope
                                    unit="vol">xxiii</biblScope>, <biblScope unit="pp"
                                    >499</biblScope></bibl>).</note>, надеюсь вас увидеть в добром
                        здоровье. Мне приятно слышать, что вы учитесь хорошо. Заочно обнимаю вас
                        всех.</p>
                    <closer><signed rend="inline">Прощайте, Бог с вами.
                        <persName ref="people.xml#cat01" rend="inline">Екатерина.</persName></signed></closer>
                </body>
            </text>
            <text type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <body>
                    <opener rend="right"><dateline><date when-custom="1789-09-12">September 12th
                                1789.</date></dateline><salute rend="inline">Dearest
                            granddaughter!</salute></opener>
                    <p>When your little sister recovers, I hope to see you in good health. I am
                        pleased to hear that you are studying well. I embrace you all from afar.</p>
                    <closer><signed rend="inline">Farewell, God be with you.
                        <persName rend="inline">Catherine.</persName></signed></closer>
                </body>
            </text>
